              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PLA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  Penfold-Leiss method was used for unfolding the",
                " information on   reaction    cross    section    from",
                " experimental yield  curve  measured in steps of 172.5",
                " keV from threshold to 14.5 MeV and in  steps  of  345",
                " keV at  higher  energies.  The absolute cross section",
                " scale was determined by comparing the measured  yield",
                " values of a (D-2)O sample and of C-13 at fixed energy",
                " value (15.0  MeV)  below  O-16(g,n)  threshold  using",
                " well-known value  of  H-2(g,n) reaction cross section",
                " of G.Breit."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The mean-square errors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The  photoneutron cross section  in C-13  was measured",
                " using bremsstrahlung    from   electron   synchrotron",
                " operated in  energy  sweeping   mode.  Neutrons  were",
                " detected by  a  multi-BF-3-counter  detection system.",
                " Decorrelated cross section ordinates were  calculated",
                " directly using a modified Penfold-Leiss analysis.  To",
                " avoid any  possibility  of  spurious  resonances  the",
                " strong negative  correlation  between  adjacent cross",
                " section ordinates,   as   it    result    from    the",
                " Penfold-Leiss method,   was   then   reduced   to   a",
                " negligible amount by using the  decorrelation  method",
                " of Crawford.  The  resultant  C-13(g,n) cross section",
                " csn be interpreted as being fully equivalent to a set",
                " of uncorrelated  cross  section  ordinates with their",
                " standard deviations, as it would be  obtained  in  an",
                " ideal monochromatic  gamma  experiment  measuring the",
                " integrated-over-angles cross   section.   The   cross",
                " section  from  threshold  to  25  MeV  shows detailed",
                " structure, some nine maxima, in agreement with recent",
                " continuum shell-model calculations."
              ]
            }
          ],
